      public static Class<?> findClassForName(String name)
      Get the Java Class for the type value in the schema.

      The Default mapping:

      anyObject
      JAVA_TYPE_BIGDECIMALBigDecimal
      JAVA_TYPE_BIGINTEGERBigInteger
      JAVA_TYPE_PRIMITIVE_BOOLEANboolean
      booleanBoolean
      JAVA_TYPE_BYTE_ARRAYbyte
      JAVA_TYPE_CHARchar
      JAVA_TYPE_CHARACTERCharacter
      JAVA_TYPE_DATEString
      JAVA_TYPE_PRIMITIVE_DOUBLEdouble
      JAVA_TYPE_DOUBLEDouble
      JAVA_TYPE_FILEFile
      JAVA_TYPE_PRIMITIVE_FLOATfloat
      JAVA_TYPE_FLOATFloat
      JAVA_TYPE_GUARDEDBYTEARRAYGuardedByteArray
      JAVA_TYPE_GUARDEDSTRINGGuardedString
      JAVA_TYPE_INTint
      integerInteger
      arrayList
      JAVA_TYPE_PRIMITIVE_LONGlong
      JAVA_TYPE_LONGLong
      JAVA_TYPE_NAMEName
      nullnull
      numberNumber
      objectMap
      JAVA_TYPE_OBJECTCLASSObjectClass
      JAVA_TYPE_QUALIFIEDUIDQualifiedUid
      JAVA_TYPE_SCRIPTScript
      stringString
      JAVA_TYPE_UIDUid
      JAVA_TYPE_URIURI
      Parameters:
      name -
      Returns:
      class if it has mapped to a type or null if not.

    • getLoadBalancingInfo

      public static org.forgerock.openicf.framework.remote.LoadBalancingAlgorithmFactory getLoadBalancingInfo(org.forgerock.json.JsonValue info, Map<String,org.forgerock.openicf.framework.async.AsyncConnectorInfoManager> serverInfo)
      Get the load balancing information from the configuration. The algorithm used can be either "failover" or "roundrobin". failover: will always try to send the request to the first server in the list. If it fails, it will try with the second etc... rounrobin: will always distribute the request to the lists of servers in a round robin fashion.
      Parameters:
      info -
      Returns:
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the configuration can not be read from info
